+## Required Options
+
+Pass `required=True` to make an option mandatory. If it isn't provided, Click
+exits with an error telling the user which option is missing.
+
+In the `--help` output, required options are marked with a leading `*` next to
+their name, with a note explaining the marker, so they stand out from optional
+ones at a glance:
+
+```{eval-rst}
+.. click:example::
+
+    @click.command()
+    @click.option('--name', required=True, help='Who to greet.')
+    @click.option('--count', default=1, help='Number of greetings.')
+    def hello(name, count):
+        for _ in range(count):
+            click.echo(f'Hello, {name}!')
+
+.. click:run::
+
+    invoke(hello, args=['--help'])
+```
+
+The marker and note are only shown when the command has at least one required
+option.
+
